Quotes Scraper

This project is a simple Python web scraper that extracts quotes and their authors from the website quotes.toscrape.com and saves them into a CSV file.

📌 Features
Scrapes quotes and corresponding authors from the website's homepage.
Saves the extracted data into a structured quotes.csv file.
Uses requests, BeautifulSoup, and pandas for HTTP requests, HTML parsing, and data handling.

🛠️ Technologies Used
Python 3
Requests – for making HTTP requests
BeautifulSoup – for parsing HTML
Pandas – for working with data and exporting to CSV

🚀 Getting Started
Make sure you have Python 3 installed along with the required libraries. You can install dependencies with:
		pip install requests beautifulsoup4 pandas
To run the scraper and generate the CSV file:
		python scraper.py
This will create a file called quotes.csv in your project directory containing all quotes and their authors from the first page of the website.

